name: Kalai B.
headline: Data Enthusiast | AI/ML Expert | Senior Software Engineer | Full-Stack Developer | Business-Focused Innovator| Aspiring Leader| AI Educator | Youth Mentor | Coding Guide
creator: False
bio:
Dynamic Technical Engineer with over 15 years of experience leading cross-functional teams in software development, data engineering, and product management. Proven track record of architecting scalable solutions, optimizing data pipelines, and delivering high-impact, customer-centric applications. Skilled in Agile methodologies and cloud technologies, with a focus on driving operational excellence and strategic business outcomes. Adept at bridging technical and business needs, ensuring successful project execution and stakeholder alignment.

KEY EXPERTISE AREAS

  Leadership & Agile Project Management: Extensive experience leading multi-disciplinary teams using Scrum/Agile methodologies to deliver high- quality solutions within deadlines.
  Cloud & Data Engineering: Expertise in AWS (EC2, Glue, Lambda, SageMaker), big data technologies (Hadoop, Spark), and database management (MongoDB, DynamoDB, Redshift).
  Solution Architecture & Integration: Skilled in designing end-to-end solutions, microservices architecture, and data integration across platforms such as Salesforce, MuleSoft, and API Gateway.

CAREER ACHIEVEMENTS

  Lead Generation System: Spearheaded the development of a comprehensive lead generation system at Rocket Mortgage, integrating data science models and multiple data sources, resulting in a significant increase in qualified leads.
  Data Integration & Governance: Successfully integrated multiple data sources into a centralized data lake at Rocket Central, enhancing product performance visibility and ensuring compliance with data governance and security standards.
 Microservice Development: Developed high-performance microservices at Quicken Loans using C# and .NET Core within an AWS environment, contributing to a 40% improvement in application scalability and efficiency, while achieving over 95% code coverage through robust testing practices.
  Cross-functional Team Leadership: Managed a high-performing team at Infosys, leading them through several product lifecycle stages and achieving substantial process optimizations, resulting in increased client satisfaction and on-time project deliveries.

name: Michael Oliver
headline: Software Engineer at OpenAI | Ex-Kojo, Pinterest, Facebook, LinkedIn, Microsoft
creator: False
bio:
I've been at Kojo for 5+ years where I've been making construction materials management faster, easier, and more sustainable by empowering our engineering teams. I focus primarily on our infrastucture, CI/CD pipelines, and developer experience, though I've been known to jump into frontend work, training AI models, security, or whatever else needs to be done.

When I'm not coding, I'm either traveling the world, hiking, skiing, or gaming. I'm a huge fan of science fiction and fantasy, so count me in for tabletop RPGs, board games, or a good book.

I grew up in eastern Canada, but moved to San Francisco, California in 2017 where I'm now a permanent resident. I've been lucky enough to travel to 31 countries and counting, which includes a 4 month backpacking trip across Japan and a stop in every continent. I have lots of stories to tell, but even more to listen to!
